      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2008 Corvette Z06, powered by the hand-assembled 7.0L LS7 V8 featuring titanium intake valves and a dry-sump lubrication system for consistent high-G oiling. This track-capable platform utilizes a weight-optimized aluminum frame and hydroformed rails, significantly increasing torsional rigidity over the base C6. Power is delivered through a rear-mounted Tremec TR-6060 6-speed manual transaxle and a limited-slip differential with a 3.42 final drive ratio. The suspension is the Z06-specific FE4 package, complemented by large-diameter cross-drilled rotors and multi-piston fixed calipers. This example presents in good driver condition, showing minor cosmetic patina consistent with its age, but remains a high-performance machine with a valvetrain that remains crisp and a chassis that is remarkably balanced.",
